# =========================================================================================
# IT Technician Scripts .gitignore
# Optimised for PowerShell (.ps1), Batch (.bat/.cmd) and general administrative scripts.
# =========================================================================================

# --- Generell Logg- och Rapportutdata ---
# Ignore generic output files created by scripts (that you don't want to save to Git)
*.log
*.csv
*.html
*.json
*.xml
*.txt
*.dat

# --- Temporary files and Backup files ---
# Common temporary files from editors and OS
*~
~$*
*.bak
*.tmp
*.temp

# --- PowerShell Specific Files ---
# PowerShell Session and Module Files That Are Automatically Generated
*.psd1
*.ps1xml

# --- Visual Studio Code (VS Code) files ---
# Ignore folders/files created by the editor, but keep important settings.
.vscode/
# Keep the following VS Code settings files that may be useful:
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/*.code-snippets

# --- Build and Binary Files (General IT) ---
# Even if you are not building applications, these folders can sometimes be created
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/
